snippet: Three rockets fired from Gaza struck southern Israel, breaking a cease-fire, drawing Israeli retaliation and prompting Israel to recall its delegation from talks aimed at ending the latest conflict.
abstract: Rockets from Gaza hit Tel Aviv and Jerusalem, and Israel resumes airstrikes in Gaza, breaking latest short-term cease-fire between Israel and Palestinian militants in the Gaza Strip; exchange prompts Israel to recall its delegation from talks in Cairo aimed at ending the conflict, further hampering resolution that had already seemed distant.

byline.original: By ISABEL KERSHNER and JODI RUDOREN
byline.contributor: Fares Akram contributed reporting from Gaza, and Merna Thomas from Cairo.

lead_paragraph: Three rockets fired from Gaza struck southern Israel, breaking a cease-fire, drawing Israeli retaliation and prompting Israel to recall its delegation from talks aimed at ending the latest conflict.

headline.main: Rockets From Gaza and Israeli Response Break Cease-Fire
headline.print_headline: Gaza Rockets and Israeli Response Break Quiet
